1st ans: Difference between compile time and run time
In compile time the source code is converted into binary code.
In run time the execution of the byte code(program) which is in binary code.


2nd ans: types of variables
Local variable-it is a variable that is declared inside a variable and is only accessible inside the method that declared it
int distance=50;
class variable-class variable defines a property of a class.
ex-public static String[] items={}


4th ans: Method- it is a collection of statements which is used to perform logic .
public static void main(String[] args)
Parameter-it acts as a variable inside the method and is written inside paranthesis.
ex-public static void main(String[] param)
argument-it is a value passed to a method when the method is called.
return type-the return type defines and constrains the data type of the value returned from a subroutine or method.
public static void main(String[] args)=void is a return type




